abstract: Disclosed herein are systems and methods for syndication and management of structured and unstructured data to assist institutional healthcare delivery, healthcare providers' practices, healthcare providers' group practices, collaborative academic research and decision making in healthcare, including through the utilization of medical devices and healthcare pools.
claims: 2. The method of claim 1 further comprising subscribing to the syndicated data feed and storing the syndicated data feed in a data pool.
3. The method of claim 2 further comprising accessing the data pool to obtain data for authorizing a medical procedure.
4. The method of claim 2 further comprising accessing the data pool to obtain data for authorizing payment for a medical procedure.
5. The method of claim 1 further comprising limiting access to the secure item based upon a privacy rule.
6. The method of claim 1 further comprising limiting access to the secure item based upon an identity of a requester of the secure item.
7. The method of claim 6 further comprising determining the identity according to a patient identifier.
8. The method of claim 1 further comprising adding metadata to the secure item.
9. The method of claim 8 wherein the metadata identifies the medical device.
10. The method of claim 8 wherein the metadata identifies a time of creation of the surgical data.
11. The method of claim 8 wherein the metadata identifies a physician who requested the surgical data.
12. The method of claim 8 wherein the metadata identifies a patient.
13. The method of claim 8 wherein the metadata identifies an intended recipient of the surgical data.
14. The method of claim 8 wherein the metadata identifies a health care professional who operated the medical device to acquire the surgical data.
15. The method of claim 8 wherein the metadata identifies a laboratory where the medical device is located.
16. The method of claim 8 further comprising manually entering the metadata.
17. The method of claim 8 wherein the medical device adds the metadata.
18. The method of claim 8 wherein a physician adds the metadata.
20. The method of claim 19 wherein publishing the syndicated data feed includes publishing the syndicated data feed to a publicly-accessible network.
